      • checkSizeRange

        @FullyTested
public static <TKey,TValue,TMap extends Map<TKey,TValue>> TMap checkSizeRange(TMap ref,
                                                                          int minSize,
                                                                          int maxSize,
                                                                          String argName)
        Tests if a Map reference is not null and its size within specified range. Size is defined as the number of key-value pairs.
        Parameters:
        ref - a map reference
        minSize - minimum number of key-value pairs (inclusive). Must be non-negative.
        maxSize - maximum number of key-value pairs (inclusive). Must be non-negative.
        argName - argument name for ref, e.g., "strList" or "searchRegex"
        Returns:
        the validated map reference
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if ref is null
        IllegalArgumentException -
        • if minSize < 0
        • if maxSize < 0
        • if minSize > maxSize
        • if number of elements in ref is outside allowed range
        See Also:
        ObjectArgs.checkNotNull(Object, String), checkMinSize(Map, int, String), checkMaxSize(Map, int, String), checkExactSize(Map, int, String)
